        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(onboard): add --daemon-env flag to openclaw onboard --install-daemon",
        "body": "Fixes #67565\n\n## What\n\nAdds a repeatable `--daemon-env KEY=VALUE` option to `openclaw onboard --install-daemon` so that extra `Environment=` lines can be injected directly into the generated systemd unit at bootstrap time — no post-onboard restart required.\n\n```bash\nopenclaw onboard --install-daemon \\\n  --daemon-env OPENCLAW_ALLOW_INSECURE_PRIVATE_WS=1 \\\n  --daemon-env ANOTHER_VAR=value\n```\n\n## How\n\nThe flag is collected into a `string[]` by Commander (repeatable option) and parsed into a `Record<string, string>` by a small `parseDaemonEnvEntries()` helper. The result is merged (last write wins) into the `environment` dict returned by `buildGatewayInstallPlan()` before `service.install()` is called — so the values appear as `Environment=` lines in the systemd unit on the very first start.\n\n## Files changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/commands/onboard-types.ts` | Add `daemonEnv?: string[]` to `OnboardOptions` |\n| `src/cli/program/register.onboard.ts` | Add repeatable `.option(\"--daemon-env\")` + pass to `setupWizardCommand` |\n| `src/commands/onboard-non-interactive/local/daemon-install.ts` | `parseDaemonEnvEntries()` helper + merge into environment |\n| `src/wizard/setup.finalize.ts` | Same merge for the interactive wizard path |\n\nNo changes to `systemd-unit.ts` or `systemd.ts` — they already render arbitrary env dicts correctly.",
        "branch": "fix/daemon-env-flag",
